Logic plays a minimal role here .
More important are what <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">LSI</ENAMEX> calls `` psychological anchors '' -- a few focal points calculated to appeal to the jury on a gut level .
In <ENAMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">one</ENAMEX> personal - injury case , a woman claimed she had been injured when she slipped in a pool , but the fall did n't explain why <ENAMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">one</ENAMEX> of her arms was discolored bluish .
